unittitle_ssm: George Irving title abstract and deed
abstract_ssm: One photocopy of a title abstract granting farmland in Flushing, Queens County, N.Y., commonly known as Willetts Neck, to George Irving, and one photocopy of a deed from Irving to the United States Government for the sale of the land.  The title abstract includes a history of the ownership of the property stretching back to 1798.  The original documents both date from 1857.
